                <div class="card-body">
                    <b>January 7, 2022: </b>The 101st Annual Meeting of the Transportation Research Board (TRB AM) will be held in-person at the Walter E Washington Convention Center in Washington, DC from January 9-13, 2022. This is the largest gathering of transportation researchers, practitioners, policymakers, and enthusiasts in the world. Several participants from Civil and Environmental Engineering at the University of Pittsburgh will be participating at the event. These include (co-authors affiliated with Pitt at the time of the conference or who performed the research while at Pitt are indicated with a *):
              <ol>
                  <li>Dr. Lucio Salles de Salles* and Dr. Sushobhan Sen*, Co-Directors of Communication at the International Society for Concrete Pavements (ISCP), will participate in the Society's annual board and open membership meeting</li>
                  <li>Dr. Julie Vandenbossche* will preside over a meeting of AKP20(1) - Subcommittee on Advanced Concrete Pavement Modeling</li>
                  <li>Dr. Sushobhan Sen* will preside over a breakout session at a meeting of AKP00(2) - Sustainable and Resilient Pavements Subcommittee</li>
                  <li>Graduate students Haoran Li*, Zhe Wan*, Katelyn Kosar*, and Charles Donnelly* will be presenting their research at the Three-Minute Thesis (TMT) Competition</li>
                  <li>Zhe Wan*, Dr. Lucio Salles de Salles*, and Dr. Lev Khazanovich* will present a paper on "Poroelastic modeling of pore pressure development in the pavement thawing subgrade layer"</li>
                  <li>Dr. Lev Khazanovich*, Katelyn Kosar*, and Bernard Izevbekhai will present a poster on "Evaluation of Long-Term Impacts of Early Opening of Concrete Pavements"</li>
                  <li>Dr. Lucio Salles de Salles* and Dr. Lev Khazanovich* will present a poster on "Local Evaluation of Concrete Pavement Performance Model Considering Rehabilitation"</li>
                  <li>Dr. Lev Khazanovich*, Dr. Julie Vandenbossche*, Dr. Lucio Salles de Salles*, and Thomas R Burnham will present a paper on "Mechanistic-Empirical Model for Cracking Prediction in Unbonded Concrete Overlays on Concrete Pavements"</li>
                  <li>Charles Donnelly* and Dr. Julie Vandenbossche* will present their work on "Quantification of damage accumulation around dowels"</li>
                  <li>Haoran Li* and Dr. Lev Khazanovich* will present a poster on "Multi-Gene Genetic Programming Extension of AASHTO M-E for Design of Low-Volume Concrete Pavements"</li>
                  <li>Sarah Stolte, Linda Pierce, Nicholas Weitzel, Jose Medina, Dr. Sushobhan Sen*, Gail Scott, and Dr. Jeffery Roesler will present a paper on "Field and Laboratory Evaluation of In-Service Bonded Concrete Overlays on Asphalt"</li>
                  <li>Javier García Mainieri, Dr. Sushobhan Sen*, Dr. Jeffery Roesler, and Dr. Imad Al Qadi will present a poster on "Albedo Change Mechanism of Asphalt Concrete Surfaces"</li>
